WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:02.734
-This is your son?
-Yes, ma'am.

00:02.800 --> 00:04.367
You gave him a truck?

00:04.433 --> 00:06.300
I told him,
I would give him that truck,

00:06.367 --> 00:08.500
till you get a job,
get back and forth.

00:08.567 --> 00:10.667
I get a call saying
my truck had been abandoned

00:10.734 --> 00:11.734
on the side of the road.

00:11.800 --> 00:13.734
Is that the way it happened?

00:13.800 --> 00:15.967
Well, it's something
like that, ma'am.

00:16.033 --> 00:17.867
[Judy chuckles] Does it look--

00:17.934 --> 00:19.600
does it look like I believe him?

00:19.667 --> 00:21.633
[narrator]
<i>This is </i>Judy Justice.

00:21.700 --> 00:24.967
[theme music]

00:39.133 --> 00:41.667
<i>James Stewart II</i>
<i>is suing his son,</i>

00:41.734 --> 00:45.300
<i>James Stewart III,</i>
<i>for tow and impound fees,</i>

00:45.367 --> 00:48.433
<i>traffic tickets, and toll charges.</i>

00:48.500 --> 00:50.367
[Kevin] Court, come to order.
All rise.

00:51.400 --> 00:52.767
Be seated, please.

00:52.834 --> 00:53.867
-[Kevin] Hello, Judge.
-Good morning.

00:53.934 --> 00:57.433
Case number 1045.
Stewart versus Stewart.

00:57.500 --> 00:59.567
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

00:59.633 --> 01:01.233
Mr. Stewart, this is your son?

01:01.300 --> 01:02.333
Yes, ma'am.

01:02.400 --> 01:03.467
[Judy] How old is he?

01:03.533 --> 01:04.467
He's 32.

01:04.533 --> 01:05.900
[Judy] Your claim
is that he owes you

01:05.967 --> 01:07.667
certain parking fines,

01:07.734 --> 01:11.066
traffic tickets,
impound fees for a truck

01:11.133 --> 01:15.467
that you either gave him,
or he borrowed.

01:15.533 --> 01:17.767
What I gather
from your complaint is,

01:17.834 --> 01:20.934
you became aware that there was
a warrant outstanding

01:21.000 --> 01:22.166
for your son's arrest.

01:22.233 --> 01:23.333
Uh, yes, ma'am.

01:23.400 --> 01:24.967
[Judy] When did that occur?

01:25.033 --> 01:28.834
On the first of June of 2020,
uh, I had a City Marshal

01:28.900 --> 01:30.700
from the North Richland Hills
Police Department

01:30.767 --> 01:34.166
knock on my door looking
for my son, stating that--

01:34.233 --> 01:35.433
[Judy] Don't tell me what he said.

01:35.500 --> 01:38.367
Are you aware that there was
an outstanding warrant

01:38.433 --> 01:39.367
for your arrest, Mr. Stewart?

01:39.433 --> 01:41.367
Uh, not until that time.

01:41.433 --> 01:44.233
[Judy] Okay. Did you become aware,
subsequently,

01:44.300 --> 01:45.834
-what that warrant was for?
-Yes, ma'am.

01:45.900 --> 01:47.066
What was it for?

01:47.133 --> 01:48.033
Traffic tickets.

01:48.100 --> 01:49.734
[Judy] What kind of traffic tickets?

01:49.800 --> 01:50.734
[James III] No insurance.

01:50.800 --> 01:53.433
No insurance on wha-- [chuckles],

01:53.500 --> 01:55.000
no insurance on what?

01:55.066 --> 01:57.633
On the previous vehicle.
Not the...

01:57.700 --> 02:00.667
on the previous vehicle
that I'd owned, uh...

02:00.734 --> 02:02.867
-[Judy] Okay. Okay, Mr. Stewart.
-This was a few years ago.

02:02.934 --> 02:07.133
So, you say that there
was a no-insurance ticket.

02:07.200 --> 02:09.066
-One or more than one?
-Just one.

02:09.133 --> 02:10.600
[Judy]
Now, I'd like you to tell me,

02:10.667 --> 02:12.800
since you say it was
a couple of years ago,

02:12.867 --> 02:13.800
I'd like you to tell me

02:13.867 --> 02:17.333
what the specific circumstances
were of no insurance,

02:17.400 --> 02:20.367
because, you know,
as a thinking person,

02:20.433 --> 02:24.100
I'm driving along,
and for no reason,

02:24.166 --> 02:27.367
a police car pulls me over and says,

02:27.433 --> 02:29.734
I'd like to see
your insurance card.

02:29.800 --> 02:32.166
Now, I've lived
seven-plus decades.

02:32.233 --> 02:33.166
[James III] Yes, ma'am.

02:33.233 --> 02:36.133
I've been driving
six-plus decades.

02:36.200 --> 02:38.233
That's never happened to me.

02:38.300 --> 02:40.600
Ever been pulled over
for an insurance card?

02:40.667 --> 02:42.367
No, ma'am.

02:42.433 --> 02:44.600
Ever been pulled over
for an insurance card?

02:44.667 --> 02:45.900
No.

02:45.967 --> 02:46.967
Kevin?

02:47.033 --> 02:49.367
No.

02:49.433 --> 02:51.600
Hundred years here
of driving.

02:51.667 --> 02:53.266
-[James III] Right.
-[Kevin chuckles]

02:53.333 --> 02:56.033
[Judy] So, you want to tell me
the circumstances how,

02:56.100 --> 02:58.600
somehow, your car
was pulled over

02:58.667 --> 03:00.500
for a lack of an insurance card?

03:00.567 --> 03:03.000
I didn't have my insurance card
on me at the time.

03:03.066 --> 03:05.633
And because I didn't have it, they,
um, I was cited for it.

03:05.700 --> 03:06.767
No, no, no, no.

03:06.834 --> 03:08.333
They pulled you over
for something.

03:08.400 --> 03:10.367
What did they pull you over for?

03:10.433 --> 03:12.033
Uh, I think at the time,
it was for--

03:12.100 --> 03:13.600
[Judy] No, no, think hard.

03:13.667 --> 03:14.967
The questions
are going to get harder.

03:15.033 --> 03:16.500
-[James III] Yes, ma'am.
-Mr. Stewart--

03:16.567 --> 03:18.433
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] I'm one of those people

03:18.500 --> 03:19.633
that you can't get over.

03:19.700 --> 03:21.000
-[James III] Yes, ma'am.
-Got it?

03:21.066 --> 03:21.900
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] All right.

03:21.967 --> 03:24.266
So, what were you
pulled over for?

03:24.333 --> 03:26.033
Not signaling at a red light.

03:26.100 --> 03:27.834
[Judy] Oh, well,
that's pretty benign.

03:27.900 --> 03:32.333
Not signaling on a red light.
Was that ticket dismissed?

03:32.400 --> 03:33.967
Uh, no, ma'am. It was not.

03:34.033 --> 03:36.967
Okay. Now, at the time
that you had no insurance,

03:37.033 --> 03:38.633
did you have a driver's license?

03:38.700 --> 03:39.767
Yes, ma'am.

03:39.834 --> 03:40.767
[Judy] A valid driver's license?

03:40.834 --> 03:41.767
Yes, ma'am.

03:41.834 --> 03:43.433
[Judy] Did you only get one ticket?

03:43.500 --> 03:45.200
Uh, yes, ma'am.
Just for the no insurance.

03:45.266 --> 03:47.834
[Judy] Did you subsequently
get insurance?

03:47.900 --> 03:49.166
Yes, ma'am.
After that, I did.

03:49.233 --> 03:50.734
[Judy] With what company?

03:50.800 --> 03:51.734
[James III] GEICO.

03:51.800 --> 03:52.834
[Judy] And what kind of car
was that?

03:52.900 --> 03:55.467
Uh, a 1997 Ford F150.

03:55.533 --> 03:58.333
Oh, that's the same year
of the-- the car.

03:59.667 --> 04:01.633
Does it look like
I'm having trouble with him?

04:01.700 --> 04:02.967
-[James II] Uh...
-I'm enjoying myself.

04:03.033 --> 04:06.166
Oh, okay. Okay.

04:06.233 --> 04:09.734
Now, that's the same year
and make of car

04:09.800 --> 04:12.300
that's in question.
So, you had a truck,

04:12.367 --> 04:14.633
just like your father
gave you before?

04:14.700 --> 04:15.734
Similar. Yes, ma'am.

04:15.800 --> 04:17.166
[Judy] Not similar, same year.

04:17.233 --> 04:18.800
Same year, same make.

04:18.867 --> 04:20.066
-[Judy] Same year--
-Same model.

04:20.133 --> 04:23.900
[Judy] Same make, same model.
What-- [laughs],

04:23.967 --> 04:27.900
Mr. Stewart, does it look--
does it look like I believe him?

04:27.967 --> 04:29.133
-Uh, no, ma'am.
-[Judy] Look at this.

04:29.200 --> 04:31.100
Does it look like I believe him?

04:31.166 --> 04:33.200
He's making it up
as he's going along.

04:33.266 --> 04:36.900
So, it's sort of joyous
for me to be able to do this.

04:36.967 --> 04:38.533
Oh, okay.
You're the judge,

04:38.600 --> 04:39.500
-yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] How many--

04:39.567 --> 04:41.734
Do you have a copy
of the warrant?

04:41.800 --> 04:42.900
Well, all I have here, Your Honor,

04:42.967 --> 04:45.734
is what the, is what
the City Marshal left me.

04:45.800 --> 04:47.166
May I see it, please?

04:50.333 --> 04:51.934
And he had, uh...

04:52.000 --> 04:53.500
Shh.

04:55.900 --> 04:58.400
Well, how much
was the total fine

04:58.467 --> 05:00.700
for this alleged
one ticket, sir?

05:00.767 --> 05:03.066
Uh, I think it was close
to 1,500 dollars, ma'am.

05:03.133 --> 05:06.633
In any event, now I know
with whom I'm dealing,

05:06.700 --> 05:07.533
I'm going to come back to you.

05:07.600 --> 05:10.800
So, this Marshal came to your door
looking for your son.

05:10.867 --> 05:12.300
Your son, at that time, according to you,

05:12.367 --> 05:13.767
wasn't living with you?

05:13.834 --> 05:15.233
-Correct.
-[Judy] But you were aware

05:15.300 --> 05:16.967
that this was not the first time

05:17.033 --> 05:19.233
the Marshals came looking for him.

05:19.300 --> 05:21.233
Uh, well, I was informed

05:21.300 --> 05:23.133
that he had already talked
to the Marshal,

05:23.200 --> 05:25.867
and he had made previous plans
to show up.

05:25.934 --> 05:27.133
[Judy] No, I'm talking about

05:27.200 --> 05:29.200
with regard to a total other matter.

05:29.266 --> 05:31.567
Did you ever have a warrant
issued for you, sir,

05:31.633 --> 05:33.300
for non-payment
of child support?

05:33.367 --> 05:35.467
Uh, no, ma'am.
that's not necessarily...

05:35.533 --> 05:36.533
What do you mean,
"not necessarily"?

05:36.600 --> 05:38.233
Well, there wasn't
a warrant issued for my arrest.

05:38.300 --> 05:41.233
Uh, I was in court
when I got arrested for it.

05:41.300 --> 05:43.166
[Judy] Okay.
So you were in court.

05:43.233 --> 05:45.967
What court were you in and when,
when you got arrested

05:46.033 --> 05:47.667
for non-payment
of child support?

05:47.734 --> 05:49.567
It was, uh, Family Court,

05:49.633 --> 05:54.633
and it was in 2019.
Uh, February 2019.

05:54.700 --> 05:57.233
Okay, now, somebody
came and arrested you

05:57.300 --> 05:58.767
while you were
in the courthouse?

05:58.834 --> 06:00.700
They actually made
a ruling right there,

06:00.767 --> 06:02.934
uh, and-and arrested me
as soon as they made the ruling.

06:03.000 --> 06:05.600
Oh, no, that-that wasn't
a warrant for your arrest, sir.

06:05.667 --> 06:08.100
The judge found that you were
in contempt of a court order.

06:08.166 --> 06:09.133
Yes, ma'am.

06:09.200 --> 06:11.867
That sounds more like it.
So, you went before a judge.

06:11.934 --> 06:14.367
The judge had given you time
to pay your child support.

06:14.433 --> 06:15.367
You did not.

06:15.433 --> 06:17.166
How many chances
did the judge give you

06:17.233 --> 06:18.600
to pay your child support?

06:18.667 --> 06:19.700
Not too many, Your Honor.

06:19.767 --> 06:22.734
[Judy] Not too many.
More than two, or less than two?

06:22.800 --> 06:24.033
Uh, less than two.

06:24.100 --> 06:25.266
[Judy] No, it didn't happen.

06:25.333 --> 06:26.967
You were told to pay
your child support,

06:27.033 --> 06:28.400
there's no question about that.

06:28.467 --> 06:30.300
Nobody arrests somebody
the second time

06:30.367 --> 06:32.667
they didn't pay
their child support.

06:32.734 --> 06:35.133
How many times
were you given a chance

06:35.200 --> 06:37.266
to start paying
your child support?

06:37.333 --> 06:39.333
I was actually battling
this for, it was a--

06:39.400 --> 06:43.200
it was a two-year deal that
I battled with my ex and, uh

06:43.266 --> 06:44.967
No, the judge had made--
not the battle with your ex.

06:45.033 --> 06:46.433
The judge had made an order.

06:46.500 --> 06:49.433
The judge had ruled that you're
supposed to pay this amount,

06:49.500 --> 06:51.133
either in permanent child support,

06:51.200 --> 06:53.667
or temporary child support.
You didn't pay it.

06:53.734 --> 06:55.367
Judge said, "I'm going to give
you another chance to pay it."

06:55.433 --> 06:57.266
I mean, I was in that court
for a quarter of a century.

06:57.333 --> 06:59.200
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] I know the routine.

06:59.266 --> 07:01.033
It's a pretty set routine.

07:01.100 --> 07:03.066
Said, come back,
pay the child support.

07:03.133 --> 07:04.900
You didn't come back,
pay the child support.

07:04.967 --> 07:06.567
-[Judy] You didn't--
-It was twice, Your Honor.

07:06.633 --> 07:08.567
Two times. The first time
they gave me a warning,

07:08.633 --> 07:09.900
the second time
they arrested me.

07:09.967 --> 07:13.333
Oh, okay.
Well, so you got fair warning.

07:13.400 --> 07:14.333
I guess you could say that.

07:14.400 --> 07:16.166
[Judy] Fair warning.
Okay. So, they arrested you.

07:16.233 --> 07:17.433
Did you spend time in jail?

07:17.500 --> 07:18.633
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] How much time?

07:18.700 --> 07:19.800
Seven months.

07:22.500 --> 07:23.734
[Judy]
You come from the State of--?

07:23.800 --> 07:24.800
Texas.

07:24.867 --> 07:26.834
Texas. They don't fool around in Texas.

07:26.900 --> 07:27.967
-No, ma'am, they do not.
-[audience laughs]

07:28.033 --> 07:30.867
[theme music]

07:30.934 --> 07:33.200
'Cause what you're
asking me to believe

07:33.266 --> 07:35.734
is that you paid off
the 19,000 dollars

07:35.800 --> 07:37.700
in back child support.

07:37.767 --> 07:39.233
Take a deep breath,

07:39.300 --> 07:43.500
and say something
that we can understand.

07:48.033 --> 07:49.367
[theme music]

07:54.266 --> 07:56.734
[narrator] <i>James Stewart II</i>
<i>claims his son,</i>

07:56.800 --> 07:58.467
<i>James Stewart III,</i>

07:58.533 --> 08:01.500
<i>owes for towing charges,</i>
<i>impound fees,</i>

08:01.567 --> 08:04.800
<i>and traffic tickets he received</i>
<i>while driving his dad's car.</i>

08:04.867 --> 08:07.266
Now, how much
child support did you owe?

08:07.333 --> 08:09.600
Uh, a little under 19,000 dollars.

08:09.667 --> 08:12.266
[laughs]

08:12.333 --> 08:13.700
How old is the child?

08:13.767 --> 08:14.867
Uh, 14 now.

08:14.934 --> 08:17.200
[Judy] And what was the amount
of the child support order

08:17.266 --> 08:18.633
that you were supposed to pay?

08:18.700 --> 08:22.300
It was, uh, I had to make
weekly payments of 165 dollars,

08:22.367 --> 08:23.400
is what I think it was.

08:23.467 --> 08:25.667
Sounds like you didn't
make a few payments

08:25.734 --> 08:28.300
if your arrears were up to 19,000 dollars.

08:28.367 --> 08:30.533
Well, something like that, ma'am.
Yes, ma'am.

08:30.600 --> 08:31.533
[Judy] Hmm-mm.

08:31.600 --> 08:32.800
[James III]
Over a period of three years,

08:32.867 --> 08:34.900
it's just missed payments periodically

08:34.967 --> 08:37.533
because of loss of job
or whatever reason.

08:37.600 --> 08:39.400
Do you still owe the 19,000?

08:39.467 --> 08:40.734
No, ma'am.

08:40.800 --> 08:41.767
[Judy] Did you pay it?

08:41.834 --> 08:42.800
Yes, ma'am.

08:42.867 --> 08:43.967
Over a two-year period?

08:44.033 --> 08:45.934
Over about two
and a half years. Yes, ma'am.

08:46.000 --> 08:47.400
[Judy] Anybody help you
make the payments?

08:47.467 --> 08:48.400
No, ma'am.

08:48.467 --> 08:50.433
Was this the first time
you spent time in jail?

08:50.500 --> 08:51.467
Yes, ma'am.

08:51.533 --> 08:52.867
Silly, right?

08:52.934 --> 08:53.900
Very.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.133
How much did you owe
on the parking tickets?

08:56.200 --> 08:57.166
Fifteen hundred?

08:57.233 --> 08:58.333
Uh, 1,500. Yes, ma'am.

08:58.400 --> 08:59.700
[Judy] Did you father call
and tell you

08:59.767 --> 09:01.233
that they were looking for you?

09:01.300 --> 09:02.300
[James III]
Yes, ma'am. He did.

09:02.367 --> 09:04.333
[Judy] And do you remember
what day he called you?

09:04.400 --> 09:05.700
Was it June 1st?

09:05.767 --> 09:08.266
Uh, it-it was around
the 1st of June. Yes, ma'am.

09:08.333 --> 09:09.266
Do you remember
the conversation

09:09.333 --> 09:10.600
that you had with your father?

09:10.667 --> 09:12.100
Uh, it was brief.

09:12.166 --> 09:13.467
Well, relay it to me.

09:13.533 --> 09:14.967
"Uh, son, they came here
looking for you

09:15.033 --> 09:17.567
for warrants.
You need to get on paying this."

09:17.633 --> 09:19.767
I then told him because
I was going through,

09:19.834 --> 09:23.033
uh, a divorce, my mother
had just passed away as well.

09:23.100 --> 09:24.300
I was also in between jobs,

09:24.367 --> 09:27.300
having just got out
from the child support thing.

09:27.367 --> 09:29.600
And I told him, "You know, I-I--
I'm going to get on this,

09:29.667 --> 09:32.367
but I can't pay it until
I get a job and get money."

09:32.433 --> 09:33.633
He then told me, uh,

09:33.700 --> 09:34.800
"Well, we need to get this
taken care of

09:34.867 --> 09:37.000
because I don't need them
coming by my house like this."

09:37.066 --> 09:38.033
And we went down there

09:38.100 --> 09:39.633
and-and he made
the initial payment.

09:39.700 --> 09:40.767
[Judy] And how much was that?

09:40.834 --> 09:42.367
Three hundred and
eighty-five dollars, I think.

09:42.433 --> 09:44.367
Excuse me, Judge.
I gave him 400.

09:44.433 --> 09:47.100
He never gave me back
my change though.

09:47.166 --> 09:48.734
-[chuckles]
-[audience chuckles]

09:48.800 --> 09:50.533
Well, that's your debt,
correct?

09:50.600 --> 09:51.567
Yes, ma'am.

09:51.633 --> 09:52.867
[Judy] Well, that still leaves
a lot of money.

09:52.934 --> 09:55.567
That still leaves
about 1,200 dollars.

09:55.633 --> 09:56.567
Yes, ma'am.

09:56.633 --> 09:57.667
Did you pay it?

09:57.734 --> 09:59.433
Uh, yes, ma'am.
Over a period of time.

09:59.500 --> 10:02.500
[Judy] Well, I want you to think
about the answer to that again.

10:02.567 --> 10:04.600
Did you pay the 1,200 dollars?

10:04.667 --> 10:05.834
Yes.

10:07.367 --> 10:08.800
Not all at once.

10:08.867 --> 10:11.800
[Judy] I don't mean all at once.
I mean all of it.

10:11.867 --> 10:13.900
I did, in payments, installments.
Yes, ma'am.

10:13.967 --> 10:16.066
That was the initial agreement
with the Marshal.

10:16.133 --> 10:17.667
I understand
what the agreement was.

10:17.734 --> 10:19.533
My question to you is,

10:19.600 --> 10:22.867
did you pay off
the 1,200 dollars?

10:22.934 --> 10:25.400
Be careful of your answer,
Mr. Stewart.

10:25.467 --> 10:26.767
Yes, ma'am. I did.

10:26.834 --> 10:28.734
[Judy] When was your last
payment, Mr. Stewart?

10:28.800 --> 10:29.867
[James III]
This had to have been

10:29.934 --> 10:31.800
about 12 months ago, ma'am.

10:31.867 --> 10:32.700
Almost a year.

10:32.767 --> 10:35.300
I actually had a, they actually
ended up picking me up too.

10:35.367 --> 10:37.500
And I had to sit the rest of it
out, all the-the rest.

10:37.567 --> 10:39.066
I didn't have the,
I didn't actually have to

10:39.133 --> 10:40.333
pay the entire 1,200 dollars.

10:40.400 --> 10:42.433
I had to sit out the rest
of what I didn't pay, in jail.

10:42.500 --> 10:44.000
What do you mean, you sat out?

10:44.066 --> 10:45.200
Sat in jail, ma'am.

10:45.266 --> 10:48.600
So, you didn't pay
the rest of the tickets?

10:48.667 --> 10:49.633
Well, they picked me up

10:49.700 --> 10:51.700
