22:02.800 --> 22:04.600
Well, you know what,
I-I-I hate that.

22:04.667 --> 22:08.000
Uh, all I have in this world
is my son and my daughter,

22:08.066 --> 22:10.000
you know, immediate family,
and, uh, and I hate it.

22:10.066 --> 22:11.000
If I did this for my daughters,

22:11.066 --> 22:12.467
I wouldn't expect them
to pay it back.

22:12.533 --> 22:13.467
But it is what it is.

22:13.533 --> 22:15.633
And-and I hope
the sooner he realizes that,

22:15.700 --> 22:18.200
you know, that life's full of
bumps and bruises,

22:18.266 --> 22:20.233
then the sooner he'll,
he'll get over his dilemma

22:20.300 --> 22:21.934
and, uh,
and he'll get on in life.

22:22.000 --> 22:22.934
Hopefully, we can move on

22:23.000 --> 22:25.200
and-and keep going
as a family, if we can.

22:25.266 --> 22:27.133
It is what it is.
But hopefully, we can.

22:27.200 --> 22:29.533
I can let it all go
because it's just money.

22:29.600 --> 22:31.233
But I was trying--
it's all about principle.

22:31.300 --> 22:33.133
Money's not everything, so...

22:33.200 --> 22:34.633
[Judy] So, the question
really is,

22:34.700 --> 22:37.800
you always keep your fingers
crossed with kids.

22:37.867 --> 22:41.033
And the child is always
your child, even when you're 32.

22:41.100 --> 22:43.533
But there comes a point,
I think, for every parent

22:43.600 --> 22:44.867
where they have to acknowledge

22:44.934 --> 22:48.266
that a child is not
really being responsible.

22:48.333 --> 22:50.767
So, here's my question,
how many chances do you think

22:50.834 --> 22:54.700
that your parents would give you
under that, those circumstances?

22:54.767 --> 22:57.633
I think the lack
of responsibility is a big one

22:57.700 --> 22:59.700
because I don't think
my parents would continue to

22:59.767 --> 23:04.500
give me more responsibilities
like a car, insurance, payments,

23:04.567 --> 23:08.800
after I've been clearly challenged
in the responsibility department.

23:08.867 --> 23:12.433
So, not as many times as
that plaintiff gave his son.

23:12.500 --> 23:14.567
You got a little latitude,

23:14.633 --> 23:17.467
you're little younger
than that man

23:17.533 --> 23:21.433
who has a grown child,
and clearly who's irresponsible.

23:21.500 --> 23:24.133
But I think at some point,
every parent has to be,

23:24.200 --> 23:26.800
aside from a loving parent,
they have to come to terms

23:26.867 --> 23:30.834
with the fact that they have
an irresponsible child,

23:30.900 --> 23:32.567
and if you keep feeding into it,

23:32.633 --> 23:36.600
the child is going to continue
to be irresponsible.

23:36.667 --> 23:38.333
I think that
that's the takeaway.

23:38.400 --> 23:40.266
Yeah.
Parents cannot be enablers.

23:40.333 --> 23:41.667
Right. That's the answer.

